column13: Abstract

column12: Piston compressor cylinder - has cylinder valve(s) with regulator for cylinder throughput, with axially-movable element coaxial with valve
column13: Piston compressor cylinder has suction valves, each of which connects the suction space of the cylinder with its stroke space and is a set of successive alternating elastic toothed annular plates and stiff annular seats with radial channels for throughflow of the medium to be compressed. Pressure valves of the cylinder each connects its pressure space to its stroke space, and are similarly constructed. At least one cylinder valve has a conventional regulator for the cylinder throughput; the axially-movable element of the regulator is coaxial with the cylinder valve and fitted within it. Efficiency is increased by regulation of the compressor throughput w.r.t. the cylinder valve.

column12: Multistage enclosed piston compressor - has high pressure cylinders fitted to hydraulic motor housing with chambers isolated by seal from impeller pump inner chamber
column13: The high pressure piston compressor incorporates at least two high pressure cylinders (10) each of which is fitted to the housing (8) of a corresponding hydraulic motor. An impeller pump is also included on the housing (1) periphery of which two connected hollow chambers (7) are provided. In each of the chambers the housing of the hydraulic motor is fitted with radial clearance. Each hollow chamber is isolated from the inner chamber of the impeller pump by a sealing unit (18) which is fitted in a ring groove machined into the circumference of the hydraulic motor housing. The sealing unit is insulated from the atmosphere by another seal (19) which is also located in a ring groove machined into the circumference of the hydraulic motor housing.

column13: Disclosed is a straightway valve comprising a housing made from interconnected stiff members, closing members made as toothed plates (10) pinched between the adjacent stiff members. Every toothed plate (10) is made as teeth (11 or 12) having their roots secured to a backing (20).

column12: Valve for gas compressor reduces dead volume - has axially arranged valve plates secured with taper rings
column13: The valve consists of a number of parallel ribs with elastic metallic valve plates clamped between adjacent ribs. End segments with an outer circular edge are fitted on either side of the assembly of ribs, the ends of which are shaped to match a circle of the same diameter as the segment. The circular edges of the assembly are tapered to suit the binding rings and which are shrunk on form each side and which hold the assembly or ribs together. Air passing between two ribs forces the valve plate into the recess and so passes through the valve. Return flow is prevented by the plate sealing on the lower edge of the opposite rib.

The present invention provides catheters whose lumen may be cleared of obstructions without transducing pressure changes to the patient compartment in which its proximal end is placed. In an illustrative embodiment, the lumen is cleared by a flush fluid supplied from or to a secondary lumen, with the patient compartment isolated with a gate mechanism. In another illustrative embodiment, the lumen is cleared by a progressively expanding balloon therein.

A cylinder of a piston compressor comprises a piston movable along the axis of the cylinder, a cylindrical admission valve and a cylindrical delivery valve. The admission valve communicates an admission space of the cylinder with a working space thereof. The delivery valve communicates the working space of the cylinder with a delivery space thereof. At least one valve, for instance the admission valve has means providing the control of the capacity of the cylinder, the movable member of said means being coaxially arranged inside the cylindrical admission valve.

column13: A direct-flow valve comprises a casing consisting of hard elements connected to each other, and closing elements executed as toothed plates (10) pinched between neighbouring hard elements. Each toothed plate (10) is executed as teeth (11 and 12) fixed with their bases on a backing (20).

column12: Reciprocating compressor valve system - may be used for pressure valve or suction valve and has radial outlet grooves in seat ring (OE 15.6.75)
column13: A pressure and suction valve for a reciprocating compressor exhibits a limited throughflow resistance and permits a reduction in the clearance volume. It contains a set of successively arranged valve elements each of which comprises a valve seat ring (3) and at least one flexible valve plate (4). In each valve seat ring radially running, groove-like outlet channels (17) are provided between the inlet channels (10), and are open relative to the opposite cylinder surface. The valve plate (4) has radially running teeth (19) which cover the inlet channels whereas the spaces between the teeth coincide with the outlet channels.

column12: Movable valve closure for piston compressor - has tongues covering inlet channel ends and valve seat plates provided with outlet channels
column13: The piston compressor pressure or suction valve comprises an assembly of valve seat plates tightly pressed together. The facing surfaces have several straight inlet channels and an outlet slot running over the whole plate length. The edges of the inlet channels serve as valve seats and the outlet slot as a stroke limiting stop for the closure pieces. The movable ends of the closure pieces (1) slide into tongues which cover the end sections of the inlet channels (3). The valve seat plates (2) have outlet channels provided which are opposite the gaps between the tongues of each closure piece.

column12: MARANGONI-FLOW-INSPIRED SELF-PROPULSION AND ELECTRIC POWER GENERATOR
column13: An electricity generating system including a liquid, a rotor in touch with an interface of the liquid to gas, a fuel compartment on or in the rotor for containing fuel, wherein the fuel compartment is configured to maintain the fuel away from the interface, a magnet attached to a rotating arm of the rotor, and a coil for placing over a path of rotation of the magnet. A self- propelling device including a float capable of floating on a liquid interface, and a fuel compartment for containing fuel wherein the fuel compartment is configured to maintain the fuel away from the liquid. Related apparatus and methods are also described.

column12: MACHINE LEARNING TECHNIQUES FOR IDENTIFYING MALIGNANT B- AND T-CELL POPULATIONS
column13: Techniques for identifying malignant cell populations. The techniques include: obtaining sequencing data previously obtained from a biological sample from a subject; processing the sequencing data to identify: a plurality of cell population estimates for a cell of a first type, the plurality of cell population estimates including a first cell population estimate and a second cell population estimate associated respectively with largest and second largest cell population estimates from among the identified plurality of cell population estimates; and features associated with the plurality of cell population estimates, the features including: a first feature indicative of a size of the first cell population estimate; and a second feature indicative of a ratio between sizes of the first cell population estimate and the second cell population estimate; and determining, using the features and a trained machine learning model, whether the first cell population estimate includes malignant cells of the first type.
